      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 86: Adding host system pkg-config directories to PKG_CONFIG_PATH unconditionally can make cross-compilation pick up host .pc files. That defeats the contrib isolation and can produce binaries linked against incompatible host libraries. Gate these paths to native builds only, or remove them from the cross-build path.\n```suggestion\nifndef HAVE_CROSS_COMPILE\nPKG_CONFIG_PATH :\u003d $(PREFIX)/lib/pkgconfig:$(PREFIX)/lib/$(HOST)/pkgconfig:$(PKG_CONFIG_PATH):/usr/lib/$(HOST)/pkgconfig:/usr/share/pkgconfig\nelse\nPKG_CONFIG_PATH :\u003d $(PREFIX)/lib/pkgconfig:$(PREFIX)/lib/$(HOST)/pkgconfig:$(PKG_CONFIG_PATH)\nendif\n```",
      "revId": "fef430aba0125b02b150df9b12d02587b3a8b70d",
