      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 260: transformSwarmMessages currently invokes every loaded ChatHandler for every conversation, regardless of whether that handler is enabled for the {accountId, conversationId} pair. This bypasses the allow/deny state used by publishMessage, so a disabled plugin can still receive and transform historical swarm messages. Restrict transformations to handlers that are toggled or auto-enabled for that conversation, mirroring publishMessage activation logic.\n```suggestion\nstd::pair\u003cstd::string, std::string\u003e mPair(accountId, conversationId);\nfor (auto\u0026 handler : chatHandlers_) {\n    const auto handlerName \u003d handler-\u003egetChatHandlerDetails().at(\"name\");\n    const auto found \u003d handler-\u003eid().find_last_of(DIR_SEPARATOR_CH);\n    const bool autoEnabled \u003d PluginPreferencesUtils::getAlwaysPreference(handler-\u003eid().substr(0, found), handlerName);\n    const bool enabled \u003d chatHandlerToggled_[mPair].count(reinterpret_cast\u003cuintptr_t\u003e(handler.get()))\n        || allowDenyList_[mPair][handlerName]\n        || autoEnabled;\n    if (enabled)\n        handler-\u003etransformSwarmMessages(messages, accountId, conversationId);\n}\n```",
